# GitHub sync (required)

This project is live on **GitHub** (`graphmen/Titan-Security`) and **Vercel** (auto-deploys from `main`).

After completing meaningful code changes:

1. **Commit** with a clear message (only when the user asked for work, or they expect delivery).
2. **Push** to `origin main` so Vercel redeploys.

## Never commit

- `web/.env.local`, any `.env` with real secrets, API tokens, or database passwords
- `node_modules/`, `web/.next/`, `mobile/dist/`, build artifacts

## Push on this machine

HTTPS push may fail with SSL errors on the corporate network. Use:

```powershell
.\scripts\git-push.ps1
```

Or set `$env:GIT_SSL_CAINFO` to `.git\ssl-ca-bundle.pem` (created by the script) before `git push`.

## Remote

- **Repo:** https://github.com/graphmen/Titan-Security
- **Branch:** `main`
- **Vercel root directory:** `web`
